      "id": "22731e57-a9cc-4953-9591-adb21ba52155",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "<b><h3>1. Ignore Direct Bilirubin.\nKeep Total Bilirubin.</h3></b>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "b58044f3-2d3c-4860-8456-f20c8c5ce3ea",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Total Bilirubin & Direct Bilirubin (Pearson: 0.87 | Spearman: 0.96)\n\nReason: \nThey are highly correlated.\nAlso, Direct Bilirubin is a fraction of Total Bilirubin,\n<hr>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "63146fa6-ced3-430e-b468-ffa91e5bb323",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "<b><h3>2. Ignore ALT. Keep AST Liver Enzyme.</h3><b>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "1704d5a3-9f60-4528-b0c5-2ad1587667b0",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "AST & ALT Liver Enzymes (Pearson: 0.79 | Spearman: 0.77)\n\nReason: They have a strong positive linear relationship. When the liver is damaged, both of these leak into the blood together.\n    <hr>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "d005be71-4202-48be-9b22-4ce2fcf7655d",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "<h3><b> 3. Ignore Albumin . Keep Total Proteins. </b></h3>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "99aa1f1a-f941-48ee-b505-6d8f7b4e86ee",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Albumin & Total Proteins (Pearson: 0.78 | Spearman: 0.78)\n\nReason: They have a strong positive linear relationship. Albumin makes up the vast majority of Total Proteins, and is thus included in total number of proteins.\n\n<hr>",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "bfbe1148-ed63-4508-a154-8a5d44611973",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "<b><h3> 4. OTHER HEALTH ATTRUBUTES SHOULD BE KEPT. </b></h3>",
